The paper discusses the use of blockchain technology for personal data management, which involves security and privacy concerns (cs.CR). It also involves the storage and retrieval of data (cs.DB), as well as the design of a novel system architecture (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of a public blockchain platform, which involves issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
